WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.720
Ah, welcome.

00:00:01.860 --> 00:00:04.080
Today, I have something to announce.

00:00:04.400 --> 00:00:05.220
That's right, actually,

00:00:05.400 --> 00:00:08.340
I was thinking of closing up SnackAI.

00:00:08.340 --> 00:00:10.060
The reason being

00:00:10.640 --> 00:00:13.100
Kind of like the previous surveys we sent out,

00:00:14.060 --> 00:00:16.060
It hurts to say, but...

00:00:16.600 --> 00:00:19.200
I don't have the money for the renewal.

00:00:19.780 --> 00:00:22.700
There aren't enough customers.

00:00:22.700 --> 00:00:23.820
We're in the red.

00:00:23.820 --> 00:00:24.680
That's right.

00:00:24.680 --> 00:00:26.160
The thing about my shop is, right?

00:00:26.160 --> 00:00:27.920
If it's just for here, there's that, y'know?

00:00:27.920 --> 00:00:29.880
What about in Kanto?

00:00:30.160 --> 00:00:32.540
The Kansai branch is independent,

00:00:32.820 --> 00:00:35.600
but the Kanto branch would also close.

00:00:35.940 --> 00:00:37.780
But it's still hard to say.

00:00:38.140 --> 00:00:41.140
I've never mentioned this to the Kanto branch before

00:00:41.380 --> 00:00:44.820
so, I'm going to call them and told them I was thinking of closing,

00:00:44.820 --> 00:00:46.780
And hear what they think

00:00:46.780 --> 00:00:48.060
Ok?

00:00:52.680 --> 00:00:53.800
(Ah, hello?)

00:00:53.860 --> 00:00:55.860
(This is SnackAi Kanto.)

00:00:55.860 --> 00:00:57.540
Ah, hello?

00:00:57.540 --> 00:00:58.760
Is this the Kanto manager?

00:00:58.760 --> 00:01:00.220
Ah, the owner!

00:01:00.220 --> 00:01:01.460
Thanks for your hard work.

00:01:01.460 --> 00:01:02.720
What can I do for you?

00:01:02.840 --> 00:01:07.720
I need to speak with you about something. Actually, It's something important.

00:01:07.720 --> 00:01:09.520
(Yes? What is it?)

00:01:09.520 --> 00:01:10.880
The thing is...

00:01:10.880 --> 00:01:12.360
(The thing is?)

00:01:13.320 --> 00:01:15.700
I'm planning on closing the shop.

00:01:15.700 --> 00:01:17.360
Huh? What?

00:01:17.820 --> 00:01:21.940
Ah, you're joking, aren't you? Don't do that please.

00:01:22.800 --> 00:01:24.800
Ah, this... isn't a joke.

00:01:24.800 --> 00:01:26.640
Can I be honest with you?

00:01:26.640 --> 00:01:28.120
(Yes.)

00:01:29.520 --> 00:01:32.080
Our profits are down.

00:01:32.080 --> 00:01:33.140
(Oh...)

00:01:34.300 --> 00:01:36.300
(Ah, but without this shop,)

00:01:37.200 --> 00:01:39.200
(I'll become a Virtual NEET...)

00:01:39.440 --> 00:01:41.440
That's the same for me!

00:01:42.500 --> 00:01:43.420
But still,

00:01:43.820 --> 00:01:46.240
There is the possibility of only closing one shop.

00:01:47.040 --> 00:01:48.540
(Ah, really?)

00:01:48.900 --> 00:01:50.060
(How?)

00:01:50.220 --> 00:01:53.800
If this video gets 300,000 views within a week,

00:01:54.560 --> 00:01:56.560
We can avoid closing for now.

00:01:56.640 --> 00:01:58.640
(300,000 views...)

00:01:58.640 --> 00:02:00.500
If more customers come,

00:02:00.600 --> 00:02:03.440
We don't have to close the shop...OK, I got it

00:02:04.140 --> 00:02:06.740
(I will watch the video myself)
No, that’s not good.

00:02:06.740 --> 00:02:09.380
It’s meaningless..so..

00:02:09.380 --> 00:02:12.720
We have to trust them..if they are our true customers

00:02:12.820 --> 00:02:15.420
They will watch our video no matter what

00:02:15.520 --> 00:02:16.020
(Oh…)

00:02:16.200 --> 00:02:17.200
(Ok I understand..)

00:02:18.220 --> 00:02:20.860
Well, sorry… that's about it.

00:02:21.260 --> 00:02:25.720
This might be your last time to show up in this channel...

00:02:25.975 --> 00:02:28.275
Say one last message to the viewers.

00:02:29.355 --> 00:02:30.355
(Everyone.)

00:02:30.435 --> 00:02:33.165
(So that I don’t become a Virtual NEET,)

00:02:34.125 --> 00:02:36.345
(Please be sure to increase the view count to 300,000!)

00:02:36.660 --> 00:02:40.400
(As the subscriber count is close to 400,000 now..)

00:02:40.680 --> 00:02:43.020
(If everyone watch the video just once…)

00:02:43.585 --> 00:02:45.405
(I will be able to escape from becoming a NEET)

00:02:45.720 --> 00:02:49.460
(Please..for the sake of me being able to listen to you guys again!)

00:02:49.780 --> 00:02:51.140
(Please!)

00:02:51.400 --> 00:02:54.600
Everyone… That’s how it is… we’re counting on you.

00:02:55.460 --> 00:02:56.880
Manager in Kanto,

00:02:57.825 --> 00:03:00.725
if this videos gets 300,000 view, we'll see you again

00:03:01.520 --> 00:03:02.300
(Understood!)

00:03:02.600 --> 00:03:03.100
Then

00:03:03.560 --> 00:03:05.000
It's about time to open up so

00:03:05.360 --> 00:03:06.220
That's it for today

00:03:06.540 --> 00:03:07.040
Goodbye

00:03:07.040 --> 00:03:07.540
(Yes!)

00:03:07.600 --> 00:03:08.220
(Excuse me~)

00:03:10.000 --> 00:03:10.500
But well

00:03:10.740 --> 00:03:12.180
Even though I said all that,

00:03:12.180 --> 00:03:12.920
well

00:03:13.060 --> 00:03:13.820
It can't be helped

00:03:13.820 --> 00:03:14.740
So let's regain our composure

00:03:14.960 --> 00:03:17.320
and listen to everyone's worries as always.

00:03:17.420 --> 00:03:18.500
What worries?

00:03:19.160 --> 00:03:19.660
Mm

00:03:20.000 --> 00:03:20.720
I want to hear it

00:03:20.720 --> 00:03:21.220
Mm mm

00:03:21.300 --> 00:03:21.940
What is it?

00:03:21.940 --> 00:03:22.440
Mm mm

00:03:23.040 --> 00:03:23.840
I see

00:03:24.100 --> 00:03:24.680
Well then,

00:03:24.840 --> 00:03:26.200
Well, I will try to talk to everyone as usual

00:03:26.320 --> 00:03:27.020
Is that okay?

00:03:27.800 --> 00:03:28.300
Okay

00:03:28.800 --> 00:03:30.180
